{"id":"1806.10753","submitter":"Shuaibing Luo","authors":"Shuaibing Luo","title":"Reducing subspaces of multiplication operators on the Dirichlet space","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA math.OA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper, we study the reducing subspaces for the multiplication\noperator by a finite Blaschke product $\\phi$ on the Dirichlet space $D$. We\nprove that any two distinct nontrivial minimal reducing subspaces of $M_\\phi$\nare orthogonal. When the order $n$ of $\\phi$ is $2$ or $3$, we show that\n$M_\\phi$ is reducible on $D$ if and only if $\\phi$ is equivalent to $z^n$. When\nthe order of $\\phi$ is $4$, we determine the reducing subspaces for $M_\\phi$,\nand we see that in this case $M_\\phi$ can be reducible on $D$ when $\\phi$ is\nnot equivalent to $z^4$. The same phenomenon happens when the order $n$ of\n$\\phi$ is not a prime number. Furthermore, we show that $M_\\phi$ is unitarily\nequivalent to $M_{z^n} (n > 1)$ on $D$ if and only if $\\phi = az^n$ for some\nunimodular constant $a$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jun 2018 03:18:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-29"}
